properties.areaDesc: Taiya Inlet and Klondike Highway; Haines Borough and Lynn Canal
properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued February 18 at 9:43PM AKST until February 19 at 9:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Heavy snow. Snow accumulations of 6 to 8 inches. Winds
gusting as high as 40 mph near White Pass.

* WHERE...The Haines Highway west of the Chilkat River Bridge and
the Klondike Highway above 1000 feet.

* WHEN...Until 9 AM AKST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Heavy wet snow will be
difficult to manage. Areas of blowing snow could significantly
reduce visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snowfall will begin late this evening and
increase in intensity overnight. Haines and Skagway itself will
receive very little in accumulation as they will be mostly rain.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM AKST WEDNESDAY
